"```sql\nSELECT (SUM(CASE WHEN m.position = 'Member' AND maj.major_name = 'Business' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(m.member_id)) * 100 AS percentage_of_business_majors\nFROM member m\nJOIN major maj ON m.link_to_major = maj.major_id;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of members who are majoring in Business. It joins the `member` table with the `major` table using the foreign key relationship and applies the conditions specified in the evidence."